President Biden visited the National Institutes of Health (NIH) in Bethesda, Maryland, and delivered a speech addressing the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic. He expressed gratitude to Dr. Collins, Dr. Fauci, and the scientific community for their work in developing COVID-19 vaccines. President Biden acknowledged the challenges faced by the scientific community during the pandemic, including lab closures and disrupted research. He also highlighted the importance of pandemic preparedness and public-private partnerships. President Biden discussed the efforts his administration is undertaking to improve the vaccination program, including increasing vaccine supply, establishing federal vaccine centers, and deploying federal staff to vaccination sites. He emphasized the need for everyone to wear masks and urged Congress to pass his American Rescue Plan to provide economic relief and further support the COVID-19 response. President Biden stressed the importance of unity and collaboration in overcoming the pandemic, expressing confidence in the ability of the United States to succeed.